title: Mother found dead in Northfield home murder | 7NEWS
description: A 36-year-old aspiring nurse, Supriya Thakur, was found dead inside her family's Northfield home, with her 42-year-old husband charged with her murder. The mother, who had moved from India eight years ago, was known for working up to 80 hours a week to provide for her teenage son while studying to become a registered nurse. Her husband appeared in court and was denied bail, remaining in custody as their son faces life without his mother just days before Christmas. title: Australian probiotic breakthrough targets cattle emissions | 7NEWS
description: Australian scientists at QUT's Translational Research Institute in Brisbane are developing a probiotic for cattle that targets microbes in the animals' stomachs. The innovation aims to reduce bovine methane emissions while simultaneously increasing beef production by improving digestion and nutrient absorption. The probiotic will be trialled in cattle feed near Townsville next year, with the potential to be added to feed in powder or spray form. title: Southwest fishing ban threatens commercial livelihoods | 7NEWS
description: Commercial fishing licences in Western Australia's southwest are being cancelled as part of a blanket ban on demersal species fishing, designed to protect at-risk dhufish and pink snapper. The ban affects approximately 40 commercial fishers, including those who target abundant species like nannygai, with $20 million allocated for licence buyouts that excludes fishers who lease rather than own their licences. Affected fishers argue they can avoid at-risk species by fishing in deeper offshore waters where their vessels are already fitted with tracking technology.
